metatags.og:description: What is Unemployment Insurance?The Unemployment Insurance (UI) program provides temporary income for workers who are unemployed through no fault of their own. Eligibility for benefits is based on past wages, reason for job separation, availability and job search requirements. Claims are effective on the date they are filed and are not retroactive to the last day worked.
